\paragraph{Context}
The matrix $\Psi$ satisfies $\Psi^{-1}X\Psi = J(\lambda)$, where $J(\lambda)$ is a Jordan block. The companion matrix $X$ has dimension $n$ and coefficients $\alpha_1,\dots,\alpha_{n-1}$. Define the row vector
\[
\chi(\lambda)=\begin{bmatrix}
1, & \lambda+\alpha_1, & \lambda^2+\alpha_1\lambda+\alpha_2, & \dots, & \lambda^{n-1}+\alpha_1\lambda^{n-2}+\dots+\alpha_{n-1}
\end{bmatrix}.
\]
